# 🔹 1. What is Linux?

Linux is an open-source operating system used for servers, cloud, and DevOps environments.

👉 Used in:
- AWS EC2
- Docker containers
- Kubernetes

---

# 🔹 2. File System Structure

| Directory | Purpose |
|----------|--------|
| /        | Root directory |
| /home    | User files |
| /etc     | Configuration files |
| /var     | Logs & variable data |
| /bin     | Essential commands |
| /tmp     | Temporary files |

